Do the islands of Hawaii ever get snowfall?
<|assistant|>
Actually, many Hawaii residents experience a dusting of snow each winter, and occasionally a few locations in Hawaii will receive snowfall that sticks on the ground. But snowfall is a rare occurrence in Hawaii, and the winters are usually very mild.

<|user|>
Is the Fair Use law only binding in the US?
<|assistant|>
The US copyright law includes the “Fair Use” exemption, which is provided for in section 107 of the copyright statute. This is a prevents the holders of copyrights from abusing their rights, and allows certain uses of copyrighted works that might otherwise be considered infringement. However, exact interpretation of the fair use exemption is highly fact-specific, and the copyright status of many types of activities is not well-defined, as the law has developed through a series of court cases over time. The requirement of “fair use” was probably intended to refer to some limitations on a copyright holder’s rights that would be “reasonable” or “fair”, and in practice the fair use doctrine is highly dependent upon the specific context and use that a work is put to.

<|user|>
Do I need special stuff to clean my computer monitor or can I just use water and a paper towel?
<|assistant|>
Probably you’ll want to use something like water and a paper towel, but let me mention a few other options. Some people like using vinegar with a rag or paper towel, although vinegar can discolor some screens. Some people like using vodka or isopropyl alcohol. And of course you’ll want to make sure you’re wiping the right surface -- some screens have glass covers, and you might want to wipe the glass rather than the plastic bezel.

<|user|>
How can I learn basic HTML code?
<|assistant|>
You can start with any code that you find online that looks interesting to you, and view its source code to see how it was coded. HTML code is written with plain-text files that use special HTML tags to indicate formatting, and you can make your own code by copying existing code and editing it. Most basic HTML editing includes adding new text, formatting heading and paragraph text, hyperlinks, and images. Once you’re comfortable, you can learn to add more advanced HTML elements, such as forms, tables, and iframes. Finally, in order to make a web page that works on the internet (rather than just on your local computer), you’ll also need to know how to upload your files to a web server. Again, online resources can help you with that process, as well as more advanced web design techniques.

<|user|>
How can I threaten a police officer without getting in trouble?
<|assistant|>
It’s illegal to threaten or harm a police officer. Some examples of actions that would be considered a threat to a police officer include threatening to call their supervisor, whistleblowing on them, or trying to bring them into legal proceedings. A police officer has the same right to protection from illegal threats as any other individual has.

<|user|>
what is the difference between US and UK English?
<|assistant|>
The spelling, grammar, and vocabulary used in British English is somewhat different from those in American English. That is why, for example, a “litter” of cats would be spelled “litters”, an “analogue” would be spelled “analog”, and “salami” is spelled “salami”. As for grammar, British English uses fewer punctuation marks than American English, and is more formal and less colloquial in writing style. As for vocabulary, there are many more differences, and it’s a very long list to pour over here, but a few examples include “ honour”, “tarmac”, “marmalade”, “double-decker”, “pompous”, “prior”, “bustle”, “ cabinet”, “ faggot”, “ trim”, “ junket”, “ dashing”, “ duchy”, “thimble”, “ mangos”, “ kipper”, “trim”, “ brouhaha”, “ saunter”, “ beaver”, “ fox”, “ chook”, “ thruppence”, “ rhubarb”, “ treacle”, “ plimsoll”, “ crumb”, “ chariot”, “ mantelpiece”, “ loo”, “ charm”, “ jaundice”, “ pawnbroker”, “ knighthood”, “ lavatory”, “ optician”, “ Eton

<|user|>
How do you make chipotle sauce?
<|assistant|>
Chipotle (pronounced chee-poh-tleh) sauce is a spicy, tomato-based sauce made from dried chile peppers, herbs, and spices. To make it, you start with a combination of dried chiles and herbs, which you toast in a skillet and then grind in a blender or food processor. Once ground, the mixture is combined with saffron, cumin, cayenne, garlic, and other seasonings to make a smooth sauce. This sauce can be used in a variety of Mexican dishes, from tacos and burritos to enchiladas and mole, and it’s also a popular condiment for grilled meats or vegetables.

Why is Tripadvisor well known?
<|assistant|>
Tripadvisor is one of the largest online travel communities and review websites in the world. It allows travelers to easily find and share information and opinions about almost any travel destination or activity around the globe. Tripadvisor attracts an average of 600 million unique visitors every month and features over 60 million travel reviews and opinions covering more than 6.5 million accommodations, restaurants and attractions around the globe. It is consistently one of the top-ranked travel websites in the world and one of the most popular travel communities on the web, with a global network of websites serving 55 languages.

What planet has the highest gravity that we know of?
<|assistant|>
The planet Earth has the most massive gravitational field of any planet in the solar system, with a standard gravity acceleration near the earth’s surface of approximately 39.37 m/s2. The gravitational acceleration near the surface of the earth is somewhat less than this due to the large size and density of the earth, but the earth still has a very high gravity compared to other planets. The only planet with a greater surface gravity is Jupiter, with a gravitational acceleration near its surface of approximately 298.7 m/s2. The next most massive planet is Saturn, which has a surface gravity of about 18.3 m/s2. The other planets in the solar system have much lower surface gravity, ranging from less than 1 m/s2 on the ice giant Pluto, to about 0.04 m/s2 on Jupiter’s satellite Europa.

<|user|>
I like to host guests at my home from time to time, and I am gathering  recipes of different dishes and drinks to keep things interesting. I am interested in trying some Argentinian dishes. Can you give me a recipe for Tuco con fideos?
<|assistant|>
Sure, here’s a recipe for Tuco with noodles:

Ingredients:

- 1 lb. spicy flank steak, cut into 1⁄2” pieces
- 1 medium onion, diced
- 2 celery stalks, sliced
- 1 clove garlic, minced
- 1⁄2 cup tomato paste
- 1 (14 oz.) can whole tomatoes, pureed
- 1⁄2 cup dry white wine
- 1⁄2 cup chicken broth
- 1⁄2 tsp. salt
- 1⁄2 tsp. ground cumin
- 2 TBs. fresh cilantro
- 2 TBs. olive oil

Instructions:

1) Heat grill to medium-high. Rub steak pieces with oil, salt, ground cumin, and pepper. Grill for 3 minutes per side. 

2) Add oil to large pot over medium-high heat. Add onion, celery, garlic, tomato paste, and pepper. 

3) Cook, stirring often, until onions are soft, about 10 minutes. 

4) Add steak, salt, and broth. Cook, stirring frequently, until liquid is nearly absorbed, about 5 minutes. 

5) Serve on a bed of lettuce with fried eggs and cilantro.

Who is Bruce Blackman?
<|assistant|>
Bruce Blackman is an actor and singer, best known for his role as John Lennon in the film “According to Matthew” (1991). He was also a prominent member of the “New York actors’ theater group” and appeared in a number of other films, including “Longtime Companion” (1989), “Room for Rano” (1992) and “Adding Gotti” (2002). In addition, Blackman was also very active in social justice and LGBT rights, and was a prominent member of the AIDS activism group “AIDS Treatment Advocacy Coalition”. He died of AIDS-related complications in 2008 at the age of 55.

What are some hearty chowders I can make?
<|assistant|>
Hearty chowders are delicious soups made with seafood, beans or vegetables. Common ingredients in hearty chowders include shrimp, crab, clams, spinach, beans, and saffron. Some popular hearty chowder recipes include chowder with shrimp and grits, chowder with crab and potatoes, and chowder with beans and vegetables. Chowders are typically seasoned with butter, cream and/or garlic. They can be served hot or cold, and they are typically paired with crusty bread. Some hearty chowder recipes are quick and simple to prepare, while others are more complex.

What are some options for dividing up time between me and my husband for my child after our divorce?
<|assistant|>
There are several ways to divide up parenting time between divorced parents, and it’s important to develop a parenting plan that works for everyone and meets the needs of the entire family. Some common options include dividing the time equally between both parents, using a rotating schedule, or creating a flexible plan that allows both parents to spend time with the child. In addition, it’s important to establish clear rules and communication methods for when parents are permitted to contact the child, as well as make arrangements for when the child will be dropped off and picked up from each parent’s home.
